Data Privacy

   PRIVACY POLICY

   June 2018

   Adledge, accredited Ads Verifier business helps to achieve safer and
   more visible ad campaign between advertiser and publisher combining
   viewability, brand safety and fraud monitoring solutions.

   The Adledge Privacy Policy is intended to help users understand how
   their Personal Data are collected and used. Through this Policy, we
   want to transparently inform you and build trust between users, us, our
   clients and our partners.

   This Privacy Policy applies to Personal Data collected and processed:
     * when you visit our Website adledge.com
     * when you access your Client Portal
     * through the viewability, brand safety and fraud monitoring
       Solutions.


   DEFINITIONS

   “HTTP Cookie”: small piece of data sent from a website and stored on
   the user’s terminal by the user’s web browser while the user is
   browsing websites

   “Personal Data”: any information relating to an identified or
   identifiable natural person (‘data subject’); an identifiable natural
   person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in
   particular by reference to an identifier such as a name, an
   identification number, location data, an online identifier or to one or
   more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental,
   economic, cultural or social identity of that natural person

   “Online advertising impression”: advertisement or any other form of
   digital media that renders on a user screen.

   “Loi Informatique et Libertés”: ACT N°78-17 OF 6 JANUARY 1978 on
   information technology, data files and civil liberties

   “GDPR”: Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the
   Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with
   regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of
   such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC (General Data Protection
   Regulation) (Text with EEA relevance)

   “Tag”: code snippet supporting the Adledge technologies and loaded by
   the browser synchronously to the webpage Ads.

   “Invalid traffic”: also referred to as non-human traffic (NHT), is
   generated by non-human processes such as bots, spiders, crawlers or
   headers.


   Our Website and the Client Portal


   DATA COLLECTION

   In order to use some of the services we provide through our website or
   client portal, you may provide us with personal data like your email
   address or name.


   INFORMATION USE

   We use the personal data you provide us through our contact form or
   when you subscribe to our newsletter on our website with your consent
   to provide you the requested information or support.

   The client portal uses your personal data with your consent to provide
   you with authentication and communication services as one of our
   solutions user.

   Your contact personal data is stored as long as you are subscribed to
   our services and deleted after a 3 years inactivity period.


   INFORMATION USE

   We use the personal data you provide us through our contact form or
   when you subscribe to our newsletter on our website with your consent
   to provide you the requested information or support.

   The client portal uses your personal data with your consent to provide
   you with authentication and communication services as one of our
   solutions user.

   Your contact personal data is stored as long as you are subscribed to
   our services and deleted after a 3 years inactivity period.


   SHARING AND DISCLOSURE OF DATA

   Adledge does not use or share your personal contact data for any other
   purpose than offering you the services you are subscribed to.


   COOKIES

   Our Website and Client Portal use HTTP Cookies to collect information
   about you. To know more about the way we use cookies, please read our
   Cookie Policy

   Our Solutions


   DATA COLLECTION

   To provide the Ad-verification service, Adledge uses data collected
   from media impressions tracking on websites where the Adledge
   technology is being run.

   Adledge neither uses HTTP Cookies nor collects direct personally
   identifying data or sensitive personal data or any personal data
   explicitly targeting children.

   Adledge collects some information about the user to a website and their
   behavior using tags. Those are initiated during media load on the
   webpage. The information collected are as follows:
     * Technical information relative to the user network: IP address,
       operating system, browser type, …
     * Contextual information : urls, page content, page layout, …
     * User action-based data on impressions to provide impression
       metrics.


   INFORMATION USE

   Adledge, along with its clients and partners uses personal data for its
   own legitimate interest and the wider legitimate interest of the
   advertising industry with due respect to interests and rights of the
   individuals. Personal data are used to:
     * Provide aggregated and anonymous reports, studies, analysis
       relative to performance of advertising campaigns
     * Classify Brand safety on media impression
     * Control Invalid Traffic

   Collected data will be saved and exploited for a maximum period of 365
   days.


   SHARING AND DISCLOSURE OF DATA

   Adledge does not share personal data collected during its activities
   with other companies, third-parties or individuals except in the case
   that the following conditions are applied:
     * In the case of a judicial or administrative authority request,
     * In order to detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security
       and technical issues,
     * In order to protect against harms to the rights, property or safety
       of Adledge,
     * In order to inform anti-fraud institutions of Invalid Traffic that
       may be considered harmful to the advertising industry.


   Your Security

   Adledge ensures that the use of personal data as well as the use of
   data from partners and/or clients follows the Loi Informatique et
   Libertés and the GDPR. In that way, Adledge implements technical
   protection measures such as data minimization, anonymization, access
   control and organisational security measures with an Information
   Security Management System and a Data Protection Officer.


   Your rights

   For more information about user data confidentiality or if you want to
   request access to and rectification or erasure of your personal data or
   restriction of processing or to object to processing as well as the
   right to data portability, please contact the Adledge team via the
   company contact form.

